abstract: Authorities in Passaic, NJ, say 3-year-old Saniyah Bonilla has died; Bonilla was found unresponsive with her mother Sashalynn Rosa and her infant brother, both of whom died, in car that had filled up with carbon monoxide during snowstorm.
lead_paragraph: Saniyah Bonilla had been hospitalized after a snow-blocked exhaust pipe caused her family’s vehicle to fill up with carbon monoxide. Her mother and brother also died.

headline.main: New Jersey Girl in Exhaust-Filled Car During Snowstorm Dies
